title: 12 - The Curious Case of Kyle Rittenhouse
creator: Pod Bless Us with Bishop Jack Lumanog
subject: Podcast
description: Episode 12 (recorded 30 August 2020).  Bishop Jack Lumanog examines the curious case of Kyle Rittenhouse -- a 17 year old Illinois boy who killed two and shot a third person in Kenosha, Wisconsin is peacefully taken into custody.  However, the flashpoint for the unrest that brought Rittenhouse from Illinois to Kenosha, Wisconsin was Jacob Blake, an unarmed Black man, being shot by police 7-8 times in the back while trying to break up a fight between two women outside a home.  At issue is the disproportionate violence against Black people by police officers which has come to the fore this year during protests against systemic racism nationwide.    --- This episode is sponsored by - Anchor: The easiest way to make a podcast. https://anchor.fm/app --- Send in a voice message: https://anchor.fm/bishoplumanog/messageSupport this podcast: https://anchor.fm/bishoplumanog/support
